Deputy President William Ruto has asked ODM Leader Raila Odinga to retire and go home. He claimed that Raila has no capacity to bring any meaningful transformation in the country. Ruto said Handshake had exposed the opposition leader as an active driver of corruption in Kenya. “Now, we know the true colours of Raila, especially in counties,” he claimed. He asked Raila to take responsibility of the funds stolen in the Kenya Medical Supplies Authority scandal. “He (Raila) has no capacity to fight corruption.” The Deputy President was speaking in Mumias West, Lurambi and Kabuchai where he held a series of public rallies. Last month, Raila said he will close all corruption loopholes if elected president August 9. The opposition chief regretted that Kenyans have lost huge sums of money through corruption. He exuded confidence that he will form the next government and create wealth for all through his economic module where jobless Kenyans will benefit receive a monthly stipend of Sh6,000. Earlier, Ruto presided over the Busia County Economic Forum in Nambale that was attended by Party Leaders Musalia Mudavadi (ANC), Moses Kuria (Chama Cha Kazi) and Moses Wetang’ula (Ford Kenya). Also present were Senate Speaker Ken Lusaka, MPs Didmus Barasa (Kimilili), Dan Wanyama (Webuye West) among others. The Deputy President said Kenya Kwanza was keen on stimulating cross-border informal trade to support more livelihoods and drive the growth of the economy. “We will place small traders at the centre of our decision-making table and initiate pro-business policies that will fuel their growth,” he told the people of Busia. Mudavadi asked President Uhuru Kenyatta to take responsibility for the high cost of living. “For two years, you have not convened a Cabinet meeting. How then do you expect to make life bearable to millions of Kenyan?” Posed the ANC Leader. On his part, Wetang’ula urged Kenyans to reject Raila who he termed as a project of the State and a puppet of President Kenyatta.